                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d384">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Boutwell</persName>, Secretary of
                        the Treasury, to Mr. <persName type="to">Moore</persName>, collector.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1869-06-24">
                        <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 24, 1869</date>.</dateline>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Henry D. Moore</hi>, Esq.,<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Collector of Customs, Philadelphia, Pennsylvania:</hi>
                </p>
                <p>I have reason to believe that a vessel with armament and an unusually large
                    number of men is in your port, with the design to leave to-day or to-morrow in
                    aid of the insurgents of Cuba. Name of vessel not known, nor other particulars.
                    Have search made, and report.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>GEO. S. BOUTWELL.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
